{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.21",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 21 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:2",
      "text": "“ Listen diligently to my speech. Let this be your consolation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:3",
      "text": "Allow me, and I also will speak. After I have spoken, mock on.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:4",
      "text": "As for me, is my complaint to man? Why shouldn’t I be impatient?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:5",
      "text": "Look at me, and be astonished. Lay your hand on your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:6",
      "text": "When I remember, I am troubled. Horror takes hold of my flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:7",
      "text": "“ Why do the wicked live, become old, yes, and grow mighty in power?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:8",
      "text": "Their child is established with them in their sight, their offspring before their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:9",
      "text": "Their houses are safe from fear, neither is the rod of God upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:10",
      "text": "Their bulls breed without fail. Their cows calve, and don’t miscarry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:11",
      "text": "They send out their little ones like a flock. Their children dance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:12",
      "text": "They sing to the tambourine and harp, and rejoice at the sound of the pipe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:13",
      "text": "They spend their days in prosperity. In an instant they go down to Sheol.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:14",
      "text": "They tell God, ‘ Depart from us, for we don’t want to know about your ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:15",
      "text": "What is the Almighty, that we should serve him? What profit should we have, if we pray to him?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:16",
      "text": "Behold, their prosperity is not in their hand. The counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:17",
      "text": "“ How often is it that the lamp of the wicked is put out, that their calamity comes on them, that God distributes sorrows in his anger?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:18",
      "text": "How often is it that they are as stubble before the wind, as chaff that the storm carries away?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:19",
      "text": "You say, ‘ God lays up his iniquity for his children.’ Let him recompense it to himself, that he may know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:20",
      "text": "Let his own eyes see his destruction. Let him drink of the wrath of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:21",
      "text": "For what does he care for his house after him, when the number of his months is cut off?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:22",
      "text": "“ Shall any teach God knowledge, since he judges those who are high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:23",
      "text": "One dies in his full strength, being wholly at ease and quiet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:24",
      "text": "His pails are full of milk. The marrow of his bones is moistened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:25",
      "text": "Another dies in bitterness of soul, and never tastes of good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:26",
      "text": "They lie down alike in the dust. The worm covers them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:27",
      "text": "“ Behold, I know your thoughts, the plans with which you would wrong me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:28",
      "text": "For you say, ‘ Where is the house of the prince? Where is the tent in which the wicked lived?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:29",
      "text": "Haven’t you asked wayfaring men? Don’t you know their evidences,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:30",
      "text": "that the evil man is reserved to the day of calamity, that they are led out to the day of wrath?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:31",
      "text": "Who will declare his way to his face? Who will repay him what he has done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:32",
      "text": "Yet he will be borne to the grave. Men will keep watch over the tomb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:33",
      "text": "The clods of the valley will be sweet to him. All men will draw after him, as there were innumerable before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.21.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:34",
      "text": "So how can you comfort me with nonsense, because in your answers there remains only falsehood?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
